<item>
            <title>[LU-10213] o2iblnd: Potential discrepancy when allocating qp</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10213</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/18347&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/18347&lt;/a&gt; introduced a bug. Basically you&apos;re negotiating the number of fragments and then explicitly setting the max_send_wrs according to that number. This patch introduces the logic where if you fail to allocate the qp then you reduce max_send_wrs by quarter, but that could cause a problem where not enough wrs are available under heavy load, if you&apos;re sending multiple fragments.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="49201">LU-10213</key>
            <summary>o2iblnd: Potential discrepancy when allocating qp</summary>
